        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 12:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “Sell that ye have, and give alms,” spoken a short while before to the disciples, and applying to all times, was especially applicable to the time then being. [So afterwards, at the destruction of Jerusalem, they had nothing to lose: and their all was in the meantime laid out to the best account. The impending calamities of the time move the more prudent, not to parsimony, but to liberality. ",
